Hello Christian,
&nbsp;
This is a very common scenario — WooCommerce treats Puerto Rico as a separate country (country code "PR"), so it won't automatically fall under your domestic US shipping zone even though USPS ships there at domestic rates.
&nbsp;
Before we dig in, could you let us know what specifically is happening? For example:
  Are USPS Priority Mail rates not showing at checkout for Puerto Rico orders?  Are rates showing but you're hitting an error when generating a label?  &nbsp;
In the meantime, the most likely fix is to check your shipping zone setup:
&nbsp;
  Go to WooCommerce &gt; Settings &gt; Shipping &gt; Shipping Zones.  Check whether Puerto Rico (PR) is included in any of your existing zones. Since WooCommerce lists it as a separate country, it will not be covered by a generic "United States" zone unless you explicitly add it.  If there's no zone covering PR, either add Puerto Rico to your existing US domestic zone or create a new zone for it.  Make sure the WooCommerce Shipping Services (WSS) shipping method is enabled for that zone, and that USPS Priority Mail is selected as an active service within the WSS app for that zone.  &nbsp;
Please share what you're seeing (a screenshot or the specific error message would be very helpful) and we'll get this resolved for you.
&nbsp;
Thanks and regards,
Sibi
Team PluginHive

